  "text": "Spencer et al. introduced an imaged-based approach for seeding streamlines directly on surface-based vector fields [CITATION_1] . By using an image based approach, the technique is able to handle very complex geometry while maintaining high performance. The seeding strategy works automatically and ensures that streamlines on the surface are evenly placed. In similar fashion, a technique for glyph placement on vector surfaces was introduced by Peng and Laramee [CITATION_2] . The glyphs are evenly spaced along the surface while allowing the user to interactively control the resolution for different regions.",
